COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 98, L.D. 165
1 Sec. 2. 20-A MRSA §1001, sub-§15, ¶J, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 295, §4, is
2 amended to read:
3 J. Establish that an out-of-school suspension or expulsion may not be issued to a
4 student in grade 5 or below except as provided under subsection 9 or 9‑A or unless the
5 principal determines that there is an imminent danger of serious physical injury to the
6 student or others and less restrictive interventions would be ineffective administrators
7 and staff need additional time during the student's suspension to develop an
8 appropriate, supportive reentry plan and ensure proper staff support to better meet the
9 needs of the student upon the student's return to school; and
10 Sec. 3. 20-A MRSA §1001, sub-§15, ¶K, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 295, §4, is
11 amended to read:
12 K. Establish that an out-of-school suspension for a student in grade 5 or below may
13 not exceed 3 days and that the principal shall make every effort to minimize the amount
14 of time a suspended student is out of school.'
15 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
16 number to read consecutively.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment provides that
1199 a school board may not authorize a principal to issue an out-of-school suspension to a
2200 student in grade 5 or below unless the principal determines that administrators and staff
2211 need additional time to develop an appropriate, supportive reentry plan and ensure proper
2222 staff support to better meet the needs of the student upon the student's return to school. The
2233 amendment also requires a principal to make every effort to minimize the amount of time
2244 a suspended student is out of school.
